title: Unable to evaluate network  or analyze new videos (HDFStore requires PyTables)
body:
I am using Windows 10 with an Anaconda Env and  DeepLabCut version 2.0

I have successfully trained the network but have been unable to utilize the deeplabcut.evaluate_network or deeplabcut.analyze_videos function due to an error with PyTables


**How to Reproduce the problem**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. deeplabcut.evaluate_network(path_config_file,Shuffles=1, plotting=True)
ImportError: HDFStore requires PyTables, "DLL load failed: The specified procedure could not be found." problem importing

2.deeplabcut.analyze_videos(path_config_file,['\\?\C:/Users/PfeifferLab/Documents/DeepLabCut-master/DeepLabCut-master/KcConditional-HCandSI-DC-Lilyana-2019-02-11/videos/DC7.mp4'],shuffle=1, trainingsetindex=0, save_as_csv=True)
